### Changes in this version (7.5.1) since 7.3.2

#### New features:
 - [2026-04-29:]: increased duration on machine files to reduce check-out frequency
 - [2026-04-29:]: added network:timeout config option and implemented timeout for requests
 - [2026-04-27:]: added support for RI-J as well as RI-JK
 - [2026-02-19:]: added initial support for PySCF density fitting (SCF only for now)
 - [2026-04-22:]: servers now check cert age before refreshing
 - [2026-02-18:]: The digichem version is now printed to the main log file
 - [2026-02-02:]: added new asset binaries to install script
 - [2026-02-02:]: added new assets to freeze script
 - [2026-02-02:]: expanded available Crest definitions to include more xtb methods and solvents
 - [2026-02-02:]: CENSO can now write a single combined report from all sub-molecules
 - [2026-02-02:]: added calc_output_file_path to CENSO
 - [2026-02-02:]: num_cpu and memory are now used in CENSO reports
 - [2026-02-02:]: added inital capability to generate reports from CENSO calcs
 - [2026-02-01:]: switched some defaults for CENSO
 - [2026-02-01:]: CENSO will now use the first available Orca/Turbomole calculation when none are specified
 - [2026-02-01:]: Method_target_options now support a class to match against
 - [2026-02-01:]: expanded default supported calculation types for CENSO and CREST
 - [2026-01-30:]: added active_directory to better keep track of calculation output
 - [2026-01-30:]: added initial implementation of multi_molecule to allow some calculations to submit multiple molecules to a single calc
 - [2026-01-29:]: added general support for calculation methods spawning multiple children
 - [2026-01-29:]: added initial functionality to allow methods to spawn multiple child calcs
 - [2026-01-29:]: added result parsing for CENSO
 - [2026-01-28:]: CENSO can now take a conformers file from a previous CREST calc
 - [2026-01-28:]: added initial support for Censo
 - [2026-01-28:]: added get_result() method for CREST
 - [2026-01-28:]: added some sensible defaults for crest
 - [2026-01-28:]: added Solvation_calculation_mixin to Crest
 - [2026-01-28:]: added initial config for Crest
 - [2026-01-27:]: added initial support for submitting CREST calculations
 - [2026-01-27:]: added better error messages for when a license has expired

